Today is a sad day in the state of Illinois. I am heartbroken to hear of the passing of my friend, Judy Baar Topinka.
Judy Baar Topinka was a trailblazer in every sense of the word. Her leadership improved Illinois & paved the way for women in politics.
Never without her signature sense of humor, Judy was a force of nature. Today the entire state mourns the loss of one of the greats.

To the people of Illinois, it has been an honor and a privilege to serve as your Governor.
I thank everyone who has worked so hard to make Illinois a better place.
Illinois has come a long way in the last six years. Unemployment is down, and jobs are up. All couples are now free to marry.
We told the truth, made tough decisions and we got our state headed in the right direction.
Thank you all. I look forward to continuing our work to make the will of the people the law of the land. http://t.co/oPKuHRRH7H
